Longding
THE LAND OF THE RISING SUN
Wakka Village is one of the paramount villages of Wancho tribe, Longding District.
It is shares a boundary with Tirap District (20%) and international boundary with Myanmar (30%).
The village is being ruled by the Village Council headed by a Chief (Wangham).
It is around 45km from District HQs. Longding.
The villages bifurcated from paramount Wakka are settled in Myanmar (06-07) ,Tirap District (03) and Longding District (03).
All those sub-villages give taxes to Wakka Chief occasionally as a mother village and speak the same Wakka Wancho dialect.
