Paragliding In Arunachal Pradesh
Paragliding in Arunachal Pradesh offers a unique opportunity to glide over verdant valleys, cascading waterfalls, and snow-capped peaks. The state’s diverse topography and varying altitudes make it an ideal playground for both novice and experienced paragliders. Adventure enthusiasts from all corners of the world are flocking to the region, seeking the adrenaline rush that comes with soaring through the clouds. Paragliding has not only become a thrilling adventure sport in Arunachal Pradesh but has also found a special place in the state’s major festivals, adding an extra dose of excitement to these vibrant celebrations.
The annual adventure festival, Adventure@ Mechuka in November, attracts enthusiasts for paragliding, and even if flights are limited, there are other engaging activities during the event. For a more convenient option, Pappu Valley in Lumdung, located 19km from Seppa town, offers a safer and consistent paragliding experience. Takeoff and landing spots are close to roads, surrounded by paddy fields, and free from hazardous terrain conditions. The site’s safety, convenience, and consistency make it an appealing choice for pilots. The Arunachal Paragliding Festival aims to draw numerous pilots to Pappu Valley each year due to its optimal flying conditions, with slow winds and large mountain and flatland thermals offering ample flying opportunities throughout the day.
