The overarching goal of the tourism policy is to position
Arunachal Pradesh as a globally acclaimed, preferred,
sustainable, and secure tourism destination. The policy aims to
bolster the state's economy, elevate the well-being of its
communities, and foster growth while preserving its rich cultural
heritage and natural splendour. In this vein, the government is
poised to adopt a holistic marketing and promotion strategy.
This strategy will prioritise engaging a broader domestic
audience in the short term and expanding to international
markets over the long term, while ensuring the principles of
sustainable tourism development are upheld.
