When compared to the top ten tourist destinations in India for the year of 2017, Tamil
Nadu had the maximum tourist footfall in the domestic circuit with 20.9 per cent. On
the other hand, Maharashtra had the highest foreign tourist footfall in India with 18.9
per cent. Yet the NER with eight states accounted for a measly 0.57 per cent with
respect to domestic tourist footfall and 0.62 per cent for foreign tourist footfall
respectively, and this despite the fact that the figures are cumulative figures of the
entire region and not individual states. This reflects the disparity between rest of the
states and the NER.
